# Neurovision User Rules and Guidelines

## User Roles and Access

### Admin Users
- Full access to all system features
- Can manage all users (doctors, staff)
- Can view and manage all departments
- Can access all reports and analytics
- Can manage system settings and configurations

### Doctor Users
- Access limited to their assigned department
- Can only view and manage their own appointments
- Can access patient records within their department
- Can create and manage prescriptions
- Can view their department's schedule

## Authentication and Security

### Login Requirements
- Must use Google account for authentication
- Must use clinic-provided email address
- Must enable 2FA if available
- Must not share login credentials
- Must log out when leaving workstation

### Password Security
- Must not share passwords
- Must not write down passwords
- Must report any security concerns immediately
- Must change password if compromised
- Must use strong, unique passwords

## Patient Data Management

### Data Privacy
- Must follow HIPAA guidelines
- Must not share patient information outside the system
- Must maintain patient confidentiality
- Must report any data breaches immediately
- Must use secure channels for communication

### Record Keeping
- Must enter accurate patient information
- Must update records promptly
- Must maintain complete medical histories
- Must document all patient interactions
- Must use proper medical terminology

## Appointment Management

### Scheduling Rules
- Must schedule appointments during clinic hours
- Must maintain appropriate time slots
- Must consider doctor availability
- Must follow department scheduling guidelines
- Must handle emergency cases appropriately

### Cancellation Policy
- Must notify patients 24 hours in advance
- Must document cancellation reasons
- Must reschedule cancelled appointments
- Must follow clinic cancellation procedures
- Must update system accordingly

## Prescription Management

### Prescription Guidelines
- Must use approved medication list
- Must include proper dosage information
- Must specify duration of medication
- Must include necessary warnings
- Must follow department-specific protocols

### Prescription Security
- Must use secure prescription pad
- Must verify patient identity
- Must maintain prescription records
- Must follow controlled substance guidelines
- Must report any prescription errors

